The body of a 23-year-old man was found on a field along Durban Road in Portlands on Monday morning, while a burnt body was discovered in Strandfontein. CAPE TOWN - Two bodies have been discovered in the Mitchells Plain area on Monday. The body of a 23-year-old man was found on a field along Durban Road in Portlands on Monday morning. The police's Frederick van Wyk said the deceased had been stabbed on the chest with an unknown sharp object. A burnt body was also discovered along Baden Powell Drive in Strandfontein. (Edited by Mihlali Ntsabo) 